  "title": "Infant Care Teacher - West Region (Choa Chu Kang / Tengah / Bukit Batok)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Develop a caregiving routine and lesson plans that align with the Early Years Development Framework.</li>\n  <li>Create and utilize developmentally appropriate materials and resources to enhance a high-quality learning environment.</li>\n  <li>Document children's learning and developmental progress to inform future planning and teaching strategies.</li>\n  <li>Regularly review and ensure compliance with health, safety, nutrition, and hygiene practices in accordance with Star Learners' standard operating procedures.</li>\n  <li>Implement strategies that foster respectful, responsive, and reciprocal relationships with infants and toddlers.</li>\n  <li>Build strong relationships and partnerships with stakeholders by actively engaging with the children's families and the broader community.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Has Certificate in Infant and Toddler Care and Development (CIT) / Higher Certificate in Infant Care (HCIC) / Advanced Certificate in Early Years (ACEY)</li>\n  <li>Has registered with ECDA and attained the EY1/ EY2 certification</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>We regret only shortlisted candidates will be contacted. All applications will be handled confidentially. By submitting your application, you agree to the collection, use, retention, and disclosure of your personal information to prospective employers.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Wecruit Pte Ltd</p>\n<p>EA License No: 20C0270</p>",
